            <abstract id="ref3" label="Abstract">The 
                <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">Black Sun</title> Archive is a collection of correspondence and manuscripts sent to the poetry magazine, 
                <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">Black Sun</title> which was edited by poet, Harvey Tucker.</abstract>
        </did>
        <accessrestrict id="ref5">
            <head>Access Restrictions</head>
            <p>Open to researchers. Appointments are necessary for the use of manuscript and archival materials.</p>
        </accessrestrict>
        <bioghist id="ref8">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note:</head>
            <p>
                <title render="italic" type="simple">Black Sun</title> was a small, avant-garde literary magazine published in Brooklyn, New York from 1965-1969. It was edited by Harvey Tucker who at the time was also active writing and publishing poetry. Since 1969, Tucker and his wife, Linda, have run Black Sun Books (157 East 57th, NY), dealing in rare books and manuscripts. Contributors to 
                <title render="italic" type="simple">Black Sun</title> included Diane Wakoski, Ben Hiatt, Richard Morris, Barbara Holland, David Antin, Elizabeth Ritchie, Alice Ransom, Hugh Fox, and Duane Locke, among many others.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref9">
            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>The 
                <title render="italic" type="simple">Black Sun</title> Archive is a part of the Avant Garde Collection at Fales Library, New York University. The Avant Garde Collection comprises printed materials, archives, and other materials related to the avant-garde writing from the 1960s and early 1970s. The collection was built during that period by curators, including Mel Edelstein and Ted Grieder.</p>
            <p>The collection consists of correspondence, typescripts and leaflets. The majority of the correspondence, which is in the form of letters, postcards and invitations, is from many notable poets to the editor of 
                <title render="italic" type="simple">Black Sun</title>, Harvey Tucker. Amongst the noteworthy correspondents are Hugh Fox, Ben Hiatt, Duane Locke, Richard Morris, Barbara Holland, David Antin, Elizabeth Ritchie, and Alice Ransom. The typescripts include those for publication in Volume 1, No. 1 through Volume 2, No. 3. In addition, there are typescripts of the writings of Harvey Tucker, editor of the magazine.</p>
            <p>
                <title render="bold" type="simple">SERIES DESCRIPTION</title></p>
            <p>
                <emph render="bold">Series I: Correspondence</emph> contains correspondence to the editor Harvey Tucker. Noted correspondents include Barbara Holland, David Antin, Elizabeth Ritchie, Ben Hiatt, and Alice Ransom.</p>
            <p>
                <emph render="bold">Series II: Manuscripts </emph>contains manuscripts submitted to 
                <title render="italic" type="simple">Black Sun</title> Magazine by Harvey Tucker, Barbara Holland, James Hull and others.</p>
        </scopecontent>
